# The real hardware config is generated on the machine at install time and
# stays out of the repo (see nixos/hardware-configuration.nix.example).
hardware-configuration.nix

# Disk images never belong in git.
*.qcow2
*.iso

# Anything secret. Nothing in the repo should ever need these patterns to
# match, but they're a belt-and-braces guard.
*.key
*.pem
secrets/
.env
